WEBVTT

00:26.940 --> 00:29.740
CHAPTER XII.

00:30.260 --> 00:36.080
And the Lord spake unto Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt, saying, This month shall

00:36.080 --> 00:40.560
be unto you the beginning of months, it shall be the first month of the year to you.

00:41.720 --> 00:46.800
Speak ye unto all the congregation of Israel, saying, In the tenth day of this month they

00:46.800 --> 00:52.000
shall take to them every man a lamb, according to the house of their fathers, a lamb for

00:52.000 --> 00:52.640
an house.

00:53.200 --> 00:57.980
And if the household be too little for the lamb, let him and his neighbour next unto

00:57.980 --> 01:03.200
his house take it according to the number of the souls, every man according to his eating

01:03.200 --> 01:05.100
shall make your account for the lamb.

01:06.020 --> 01:11.000
Your lamb shall be without blemish a male of the first year, ye shall take it out from

01:11.000 --> 01:16.040
the sheep or from the goats, and ye shall keep it up until the fourteenth day of the

01:16.040 --> 01:20.660
same month, and the whole assembly of the congregation of Israel shall kill it in the

01:20.660 --> 01:21.060
evening.

01:21.720 --> 01:26.480
And they shall take up the blood and strike it on the two side-posts and on the upper

01:26.480 --> 01:29.720
door-post of the houses wherein they shall eat it.

01:30.420 --> 01:35.800
And they shall eat the flesh in that night, roast with fire and unleavened bread, and

01:35.800 --> 01:37.900
with bitter herbs they shall eat it.

01:38.620 --> 01:44.760
Eat not of it raw nor sodden at all with water, but roast with fire, his head with his legs

01:44.760 --> 01:46.640
and with the pertenance thereof.

01:47.480 --> 01:52.060
And ye shall let nothing of it remain until the morning, and that which remaineth of it

01:52.060 --> 01:54.380
until the morning ye shall burn with fire.

01:55.120 --> 02:00.320
And thus shall ye eat it, with your loins girded, your shoes on your feet, and your

02:00.320 --> 02:04.960
staff in your hand, and ye shall eat it in haste, it is the Lord's Passover.

02:06.140 --> 02:11.020
For I will pass through the land of Egypt this night, and will smite all the first born

02:11.020 --> 02:16.980
in the land of Egypt, both man and beast, and against all the gods of Egypt I will execute

02:16.980 --> 02:17.460
judgment.

02:17.820 --> 02:19.080
I am the Lord.

02:19.080 --> 02:24.840
And the blood shall be to you for a token upon the houses where ye are, and when I see

02:24.840 --> 02:30.400
the blood I will pass over you, and the plague shall not be upon you to destroy you when

02:30.400 --> 02:32.200
I smite the land of Egypt.

02:33.180 --> 02:38.700
And this day shall be unto you for a memorial, and ye shall keep it a feast to the Lord throughout

02:38.700 --> 02:43.240
your generations, ye shall keep it a feast by an ordinance for ever.

02:44.260 --> 02:49.800
Seven days shall ye eat unleavened bread, even the first day ye shall put away leaven

02:49.800 --> 02:55.480
out of your houses, for whosoever eateth leavened bread from the first day until the seventh

02:55.480 --> 02:58.880
day, that soul shall be cut off from Israel.

02:59.800 --> 03:04.980
And in the first day there shall be an holy convocation, and in the seventh day there

03:04.980 --> 03:07.100
shall be an holy convocation to you.

03:07.460 --> 03:13.220
No matter of work shall be done in them save that which every man must eat, that only may

03:13.220 --> 03:14.240
be done of you.

03:15.140 --> 03:20.800
And ye shall observe the feast of unleavened bread, for in this selfsame day have I brought

03:20.800 --> 03:26.680
your armies out of the land of Egypt, therefore shall ye observe this day in your generations

03:26.680 --> 03:28.720
by an ordinance for ever.

03:30.080 --> 03:34.780
In the first month on the fourteenth day of the month at even ye shall eat unleavened

03:34.780 --> 03:38.220
bread until the one and twentieth day of the month at even.

03:39.020 --> 03:44.660
Seven days shall there be no leaven found in your houses, for whosoever eateth that

03:44.660 --> 03:50.080
which is leavened, even that soul shall be cut off from the congregation of Israel, whether

03:50.080 --> 03:52.600
he be a stranger or born in the land.

03:53.500 --> 03:58.900
Ye shall eat nothing leavened, and all your habitations shall ye eat unleavened bread.

04:01.000 --> 04:06.820
Then Moses called for all the elders of Israel and said unto them, Draw out and take you

04:06.820 --> 04:10.220
a lamb according to your families and kill the Passover.

04:11.140 --> 04:16.320
And ye shall take a bunch of hyssop and dip it in the blood that is in the basin and strike

04:16.320 --> 04:21.700
the lintel and the two side-posts with the blood that is in the basin, and none of you

04:21.700 --> 04:24.700
shall go out at the door of his house until the morning.

04:25.600 --> 04:30.840
For the Lord will pass through to smite the Egyptians, and when he seeth the blood upon

04:30.840 --> 04:36.800
the lintel and on the two side-posts the Lord will pass over the door and will not suffer

04:36.800 --> 04:40.500
the destroyer to come in unto your houses to smite you.

04:41.060 --> 04:46.180
And ye shall observe this thing for an ordinance to thee and to thy sons for ever.

04:47.160 --> 04:52.160
And it shall come to pass when ye become to the land which the Lord will give you according

04:52.160 --> 04:55.480
as he hath promised that ye shall keep this service.

04:56.060 --> 05:01.560
And it shall come to pass when your children shall say unto you, What mean ye by this service,

05:01.860 --> 05:07.560
that ye shall say, It is the sacrifice of the Lord's Passover who passed over the houses

05:07.560 --> 05:13.080
of the children of Israel in Egypt when he smote the Egyptians and delivered our houses.

05:13.760 --> 05:16.200
And the people bowed the head and worshipped.

05:17.040 --> 05:21.900
And the children of Israel went away and did as the Lord had commanded Moses and Aaron,

05:22.220 --> 05:23.320
so did they.

05:24.520 --> 05:30.060
And it came to pass that at midnight the Lord smote all the first born in the land of Egypt

05:30.060 --> 05:35.420
from the first born of Pharaoh that sat on his throne under the first born of the captive

05:35.420 --> 05:39.020
that was in the dungeon and all the first born of cattle.

05:40.280 --> 05:46.220
And Pharaoh rose up in the night, he and all his servants and all the Egyptians, and there

05:46.220 --> 05:51.480
was a great cry in Egypt, for there was not a house where there was not one dead.

05:52.480 --> 05:58.440
And he called for Moses and Aaron by night and said, Rise up and get you forth from among

05:58.440 --> 06:04.360
my people, both ye and the children of Israel, and go, serve the Lord, as ye have said.

06:05.100 --> 06:11.440
Also take your flocks and your herds, as ye have said, and be gone, and bless me also.

06:12.540 --> 06:17.080
And the Egyptians were urgent upon the people that they might send them out of the land

06:17.080 --> 06:20.600
in haste, for they said, We be all dead men.

06:21.260 --> 06:25.540
And the people took their dough before it was leavened, their kneading troughs being

06:25.540 --> 06:31.040
bound up and their clothes upon their shoulders. And the children of Israel did according to

06:31.040 --> 06:36.580
the word of Moses, and they borrowed of the Egyptians jewels of silver and jewels of gold

06:36.580 --> 06:42.180
and raiment. And the Lord gave the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians, so that

06:42.180 --> 06:46.960
they lent unto them such things as they required, and they spoiled the Egyptians.

06:48.600 --> 06:54.060
And the children of Israel journeyed from Ramesses to Succoth, about six hundred thousand

06:54.060 --> 07:00.680
on foot that were men, beside children. And a mixed multitude went up also with them,

07:00.900 --> 07:07.160
and flocks and herds, even very much cattle. And they baked unleavened cakes of the dough

07:07.160 --> 07:12.000
which they brought forth out of Egypt, for it was not leavened, because they were thrust

07:12.000 --> 07:17.020
out of Egypt and could not tarry, neither had they prepared for themselves any victual.

07:18.340 --> 07:23.140
Now the sojourning of the children of Israel who dwelt in Egypt was four hundred and thirty

07:23.140 --> 07:29.420
years. And it came to pass at the end of the four hundred and thirty years, even the selfsame

07:29.420 --> 07:34.460
day had came to pass, that all the hosts of the Lord went out from the land of Egypt.

07:35.380 --> 07:39.720
It is a night to be much observed unto the Lord for bringing them out from the land of

07:39.720 --> 07:44.860
Egypt. This is that night of the Lord to be observed of all the children of Israel in

07:44.860 --> 07:45.820
their generations.

07:46.680 --> 07:52.040
And the Lord said unto Moses and Aaron, This is the ordinance of the Passover. There shall

07:52.040 --> 07:57.280
no stranger eat thereof, but every man's servant that has bought for money, when thou hast

07:57.280 --> 08:03.240
circumcised him, then shall he eat thereof. A foreigner and an hired servant shall not

08:03.240 --> 08:09.180
eat thereof. In one house shall it be eaten, thou shalt not carry forth aught of the flesh

08:09.180 --> 08:15.080
abroad out of the house, neither shall ye break a bone thereof. All the congregation

08:15.080 --> 08:20.500
of Israel shall keep it. And when a stranger shall sojourn with thee, and will keep the

08:20.500 --> 08:25.980
Passover to the Lord, let all his meals be circumcised, and then let him come near and

08:25.980 --> 08:31.860
keep it, and he shall be as one that is born in the land, for no uncircumcised person shall

08:31.860 --> 08:38.540
eat thereof. One law shall be to him that is home-born, and unto the stranger that sojourneth

08:38.540 --> 08:39.300
among you.

08:40.320 --> 08:45.900
Thus did all the children of Israel, as the Lord commanded Moses and Aaron, so did they.

08:46.600 --> 08:51.180
And it came to pass the selfsame day that the Lord did bring the children of Israel

08:51.180 --> 08:53.760
out of the land of Egypt by their armies.

08:55.660 --> 08:56.780
CHAPTER XIII

08:57.620 --> 09:04.020
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, Sanctify unto me all the first born, whatsoever openeth

09:04.020 --> 09:10.820
the womb among the children of Israel, both of man and of beast, it is mine. And Moses

09:10.820 --> 09:16.020
said unto the people, Remember this day in which ye came out from Egypt out of the house

09:16.020 --> 09:21.400
of bondage, for by strength of hand the Lord brought you out from this place, there shall

09:21.400 --> 09:23.060
no leavened bread be eaten.

09:24.280 --> 09:27.300
This day came ye out in the month Abib.

09:28.820 --> 09:32.760
And it shall be when the Lord shall bring thee into the land of the Canaanites, and

09:32.760 --> 09:38.020
the Hittites, and the Amorites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites, which he swear unto thy

09:38.020 --> 09:43.580
fathers to give thee a land flowing with milk and honey, that thou shalt keep this service

09:43.580 --> 09:44.440
in this month.

09:45.560 --> 09:50.160
Seven days thou shalt eat unleavened bread, and in the seventh day shall be a feast to

09:50.160 --> 09:50.680
the Lord.

09:51.780 --> 09:56.280
Unleavened bread shall be eaten seven days, and there shall no leavened bread be seen

09:56.280 --> 10:00.220
with thee, neither shall there be leaven seen with thee in all thy quarters.

10:01.320 --> 10:06.560
And thou shalt show thy son in that day, saying, This is done because of that which the Lord

10:06.560 --> 10:09.080
did unto me when I came forth out of Egypt.

10:10.020 --> 10:14.940
And it shall be for a sign unto thee upon thine hand, and for a memorial between thine

10:14.940 --> 10:20.640
eyes, that the Lord's law may be in thy mouth, for with a strong hand hath the Lord brought

10:20.640 --> 10:21.780
thee out of Egypt.

10:22.660 --> 10:26.500
Thou shalt therefore keep this ordinance in his season from year to year.

10:27.400 --> 10:36.100
And it shall be when the Lord shall bring thee into the land of the Canaanites, as he

10:36.100 --> 10:41.380
shalt set apart unto the Lord all that openeth the matrix, and every firstling that cometh

10:41.380 --> 10:45.480
of a beast which thou hast, the males shall be the Lord's.

10:45.940 --> 10:51.480
And every firstling of an ass thou shalt redeem with a lamb, and if thou wilt not redeem it,

10:51.540 --> 10:56.180
then thou shalt break his neck, and all the firstborn of man among thy children shalt

10:56.180 --> 10:56.840
thou redeem.

10:57.720 --> 11:02.900
And it shall be when thy son asketh thee in time to come, saying, What is this?

11:02.900 --> 11:08.300
that thou shalt say unto him, By strength of hand the Lord brought us out of Egypt from

11:08.300 --> 11:09.740
the house of bondage.

11:10.280 --> 11:16.020
And it came to pass when Pharaoh would hardly let us go, that the Lord slew all the firstborn

11:16.020 --> 11:20.620
in the land of Egypt, both the firstborn of man and the firstborn of beast.

11:21.140 --> 11:26.960
Therefore I sacrificed to the Lord all that openeth the matrix, being males, but all the

11:26.960 --> 11:29.080
firstborn of my children I redeem.

11:29.840 --> 11:35.200
And it shall be for a token upon thine hand, and for frontlets between thine eyes, for

11:35.200 --> 11:38.460
by strength of hand the Lord brought us forth out of Egypt.

11:39.800 --> 11:44.540
And it came to pass when Pharaoh had let the people go, that God led them not through the

11:44.540 --> 11:50.120
way of the land of the Philistines, although that was near, for God said, Lest per adventure

11:50.120 --> 11:53.880
the people repent when they see war, and they return to Egypt.

11:54.430 --> 11:59.340
But God led the people about through the way of the wilderness of the Red Sea, and the

11:59.340 --> 12:02.840
children of Israel went up harnessed out of the land of Egypt.

12:03.940 --> 12:08.500
And Moses took the bones of Joseph with him, for he had straightly sworn the children of

12:08.500 --> 12:14.180
Israel, saying, God will surely visit you, and ye shall carry up my bones away hence

12:14.180 --> 12:15.000
with you.

12:16.220 --> 12:21.080
And they took their journey from Succoth and encamped in ethom in the edge of the wilderness.

12:21.620 --> 12:26.820
And the Lord went before them by day in a pillar of a cloud to lead them the way, and

12:26.820 --> 12:31.780
by night in a pillar of fire to give them light, to go by day and night.

12:32.280 --> 12:37.500
He took not away the pillar of the cloud by day, nor the pillar of fire by night, from

12:37.500 --> 12:38.600
before the people.

12:40.220 --> 12:41.260
CHAPTER XIV

12:41.260 --> 12:46.980
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, Speak unto the children of Israel that they turn

12:46.980 --> 12:53.140
and encamp forphi-hyrath between Migdal and the sea over against Baal-Ziphon.

12:53.300 --> 12:55.560
Before it shall ye encamp by the sea.

12:56.180 --> 13:01.280
For Pharaoh will say of the children of Israel, They are entangled in the land, the wilderness

13:01.280 --> 13:02.500
hath shut them in.

13:03.080 --> 13:08.220
And I will harden Pharaoh's heart that he shall follow after them, and I will be honored

13:08.220 --> 13:14.020
upon Pharaoh and upon all his host that the Egyptians may know that I am the Lord.

13:14.540 --> 13:15.640
And they did so.

13:16.940 --> 13:21.680
And it was told the King of Egypt that the people fled, and the heart of Pharaoh and

13:21.680 --> 13:26.780
of his servants was turned against the people, and they said, Why have we done this, that

13:26.780 --> 13:29.220
we have let Israel go from serving us?

13:30.000 --> 13:35.640
And he made ready his chariot and took his people with him, and he took six hundred chosen

13:35.640 --> 13:40.200
chariots and all the chariots of Egypt and captains over every one of them.

13:40.700 --> 13:46.000
And the Lord hardened the heart of Pharaoh, King of Egypt, and he pursued after the children

13:46.000 --> 13:50.040
of Israel, and the children of Israel went out with a high hand.

13:51.080 --> 13:56.820
But the Egyptians pursued after them all the horses and chariots of Pharaoh and his horsemen

13:56.820 --> 14:03.820
and his army, and overtook them encamping by the sea beside Piah-hyrath before Baal-Ziphon.

14:04.820 --> 14:09.560
And when Pharaoh drew nigh the children of Israel lifted up their eyes, and behold the

14:09.560 --> 14:14.840
Egyptians marched after them, and they were sore afraid, and the children of Israel cried

14:14.840 --> 14:16.160
out unto the Lord.

14:16.960 --> 14:22.340
And they said unto Moses, Because there were no graves in Egypt, hast thou taken us away

14:22.340 --> 14:23.760
to die in the wilderness?

14:24.400 --> 14:28.620
Wherefore hast thou dealt thus with us to carry us forth out of Egypt?

14:29.440 --> 14:34.540
Is not this the word that we did tell thee in Egypt, saying, Let us alone that we may

14:35.200 --> 14:41.140
for it had been better for us to serve the Egyptians than that we should die in the wilderness?

14:42.320 --> 14:48.380
And Moses said unto the people, Fear ye not, stand still, and see the salvation of the

14:48.380 --> 14:53.980
Lord which he will show to you to-day, for the Egyptians whom ye have seen to-day ye

14:53.980 --> 14:56.500
shall see them again no more for ever.

14:57.100 --> 15:00.740
The Lord shall fight for you, and ye shall hold your peace.

15:01.620 --> 15:07.300
And the Lord said unto Moses, Wherefore cryest thou unto me, Speak unto the children of

15:07.300 --> 15:12.660
Israel that they go forward, but lift thou up thy rod, and stretch out thine hand over

15:12.660 --> 15:17.880
the sea, and divide it, and the children of Israel shall go on dry ground through the

15:17.880 --> 15:18.940
midst of the sea.

15:19.600 --> 15:24.960
And I, behold I, will harden the hearts of the Egyptians, and they shall follow them,

15:24.960 --> 15:30.700
and I will get me honor upon Pharaoh, and upon all his host, upon his chariots, and

15:30.700 --> 15:31.820
upon his horsemen.

15:32.660 --> 15:37.860
And the Egyptians shall know that I am the Lord, when I have gotten me honor upon Pharaoh,

15:38.200 --> 15:41.040
upon his chariots, and upon his horsemen.

15:42.440 --> 15:47.600
And the angel of God which went before the camp of Israel removed and went behind them,

15:47.880 --> 15:52.060
and the pillar of the cloud went from before their face and stood behind them.

15:52.060 --> 15:57.600
And it came between the cap of the Egyptians and the cap of Israel, and it was a cloud

15:57.600 --> 16:03.500
in darkness to them, but it gave light by night to these, so that the one came not near

16:03.500 --> 16:05.100
the other all the night.

16:06.140 --> 16:11.360
And Moses stretched out his hand over the sea, and the Lord caused the sea to go back

16:11.360 --> 16:17.400
by a strong east wind all that night, and made the sea dry land, and the waters were

16:17.400 --> 16:17.860
divided.

16:18.600 --> 16:24.060
And the children of Israel went into the midst of the sea upon the dry ground, and the waters

16:24.060 --> 16:27.420
were a wall unto them on their right hand and on their left.

16:28.220 --> 16:33.620
And the Egyptians pursued and went in after them to the midst of the sea, even all Pharaoh's

16:33.620 --> 16:36.260
horses, his chariots, and his horsemen.

16:37.140 --> 16:41.920
And it came to pass that in the morning watch the Lord looked unto the host of the Egyptians

16:41.920 --> 16:47.320
through the pillar of fire and of the cloud, and troubled the host of the Egyptians, and

16:47.320 --> 16:52.720
took off their chariot wheels that they draved them heavily, so that the Egyptians said,

16:53.060 --> 16:58.320
Let us flee from the face of Israel, for the Lord fighteth for them against the Egyptians.

16:59.440 --> 17:04.720
And the Lord said unto Moses, Stretch out thine hand over the sea, that the waters may

17:04.720 --> 17:09.620
come again upon the Egyptians, and upon their chariots, and upon their horsemen.

17:10.600 --> 17:15.420
And Moses stretched forth his hand over the sea, and the sea returned to his strength

17:15.420 --> 17:20.720
when the morning appeared, and the Egyptians fled against it, and the Lord overthrew the

17:20.720 --> 17:22.700
Egyptians in the midst of the sea.

17:23.760 --> 17:29.020
And the waters returned and covered the chariots, and the horsemen, and all the host of Pharaoh

17:29.020 --> 17:34.120
that came into the sea after them, there remained not so much as one of them.

17:34.860 --> 17:39.880
But the children of Israel walked upon dry land in the midst of the sea, and the waters

17:39.880 --> 17:43.180
were a wall unto them on their right hand and on their left.

17:44.020 --> 17:49.640
Thus the Lord saved Israel that day out of the hand of the Egyptians, and Israel saw

17:49.640 --> 17:52.340
the Egyptians dead upon the seashore.

17:53.260 --> 17:58.560
And Israel saw that great work which the Lord did upon the Egyptians, and the people feared

17:58.560 --> 18:02.200
the Lord and believed the Lord and His servant Moses.

18:04.360 --> 18:05.540
CHAPTER XV

18:06.360 --> 18:11.540
Then sang Moses and the children of Israel this song unto the Lord, and spake, saying,

18:11.540 --> 18:15.840
I will sing unto the Lord, for he hath triumphed gloriously.

18:16.240 --> 18:19.300
The horse and his rider hath he thrown into the sea.

18:20.520 --> 18:24.560
The Lord is my strength and song, and he has become my salvation.

18:25.140 --> 18:31.560
He is my God, and I will prepare him and habitation, my Father's God, and I will exalt him.

18:32.380 --> 18:35.780
The Lord is a man of war, the Lord is his name.

18:36.940 --> 18:40.240
Pharaoh's chariots and his host hath he cast into the sea.

18:40.700 --> 18:44.240
His chosen captains also are drowned in the Red Sea.

18:44.940 --> 18:46.420
The depths have covered them.

18:46.700 --> 18:48.900
They sank into the bottom as a stone.

18:49.860 --> 18:53.020
Thy right hand, O Lord, has become glorious in power.

18:53.500 --> 18:57.000
Thy right hand, O Lord, hath dashed in pieces the enemy.

18:57.680 --> 19:02.600
And in the greatness of thine excellency thou hast overthrown them that rose up against

19:02.600 --> 19:03.080
thee.

19:03.080 --> 19:07.480
Thou sentest forth thy wrath, which consumed them as stubble.

19:08.200 --> 19:13.380
And with the blast of thy nostrils the waters were gathered together, the floods stood upright

19:13.380 --> 19:17.220
as a heap, and the depths were congealed in the heart of the sea.

19:18.140 --> 19:24.460
The enemy said, I will pursue, I will overtake, I will divide the spoil, my lust shall be

19:24.460 --> 19:29.240
satisfied upon them, I will draw my sword, my hand shall destroy them.

19:29.240 --> 19:35.780
Thou didst blow with thy wind, the sea covered them, they sank as lead in the mighty waters.

19:36.960 --> 19:39.880
Who is like unto thee, O Lord, among the gods?

19:40.240 --> 19:45.620
Who is like thee, glorious in holiness, fearful in praises, doing wonders?

19:46.680 --> 19:50.640
Thou stretchest out thy right hand, the earth swallowed them.

19:51.380 --> 19:56.540
Thou in thy mercy hast led forth the people which thou hast redeemed, thou hast guided

19:56.540 --> 19:59.880
them in thy strength unto thy holy habitation.

20:00.700 --> 20:06.600
The people shall hear and be afraid, sorrow shall take hold on the inhabitants of Palestine.

20:07.480 --> 20:12.840
Then the Dukes of Edom shall be amazed, the mighty men of Moab trembling shall take hold

20:12.840 --> 20:16.560
upon them, all the inhabitants of Canaan shall melt away.

20:17.300 --> 20:22.560
Fear and dread shall fall upon them, by the greatness of thine arm they shall be as still

20:22.560 --> 20:28.580
as a stone, till thy people pass over, O Lord, till the people pass over which thou hast

20:28.580 --> 20:29.280
purchased.

20:30.280 --> 20:34.760
Thou shalt bring them in and plant them in the mountain of thine inheritance, in the

20:34.760 --> 20:40.220
place, O Lord, which thou hast made for thee to dwell in, in the sanctuary, O Lord, which

20:40.220 --> 20:41.780
thy hands have established.

20:42.480 --> 20:45.440
The Lord shall reign for ever and ever.

20:45.920 --> 20:51.860
For the horse of Pharaoh went in with his chariots and with his horsemen into the sea, and the

20:51.860 --> 20:57.020
Lord brought again the waters of the sea upon them, but the children of Israel went on dry

20:57.020 --> 20:58.820
land in the midst of the sea.

21:00.260 --> 21:05.720
And Miriam the prophetess, the sister of Aaron, took a timbrel in her hand, and all the women

21:05.720 --> 21:08.520
went out after her with timbrels and with dances.

21:09.400 --> 21:15.480
And Miriam answered them, Sing ye to the Lord, for he hath triumphed gloriously, the horse

21:15.480 --> 21:18.000
and his rider hath he thrown into the sea.

21:18.620 --> 21:23.960
So Moses brought Israel from the Red Sea, and they went out into the wilderness of Shur,

21:24.380 --> 21:27.940
and they went three days in the wilderness, and found no water.

21:29.180 --> 21:33.460
And when they came to Marah, they could not drink of the waters of Marah, for they were

21:33.460 --> 21:36.560
bitter, therefore the name of it was called Marah.

21:37.440 --> 21:41.500
And the people murmured against Moses, saying, What shall we drink?

21:42.220 --> 21:47.640
And he cried unto the Lord, and the Lord showed him a tree, which, when he had cast into the

21:47.640 --> 21:49.860
waters, the waters were made sweet.

21:50.360 --> 21:56.780
There he made for them a statute and an ordinance, and there he proved them, and said, If thou

21:56.780 --> 22:01.980
wilt diligently hearken to the voice of the Lord thy God, and wilt do that which is right

22:01.980 --> 22:08.240
in his sight, and wilt give ear to his commandments, and keep all his statutes, I will put none

22:08.240 --> 22:14.340
of these diseases upon thee which I have brought upon the Egyptians, for I am the Lord that

22:14.340 --> 22:15.120
healeth thee.

22:16.100 --> 22:22.520
And they came to Elam, where were twelve wells of water, and threescore and ten palm-trees,

22:22.620 --> 22:24.820
and they encamped there by the waters.

22:27.040 --> 22:28.160
CHAPTER XVI.

22:29.180 --> 22:33.500
And they took their journey from Elam, and all the congregation of the children of Israel

22:33.500 --> 22:39.360
came unto the wilderness of Sin, which is between Elam and Sinai, on the fifteenth day

22:39.360 --> 22:43.180
after their departing out of the land of Egypt.

22:44.200 --> 22:48.700
And the whole congregation of the children of Israel murmured against Moses and Aaron

22:48.700 --> 22:54.280
in the wilderness, and the children of Israel said unto them, Would to God we had died by

22:54.280 --> 22:59.340
the hand of the Lord in the land of Egypt when we sat by the flesh-pots and when we

22:59.340 --> 23:04.140
did eat bread to the full, for ye have brought us forth into this wilderness to kill this

23:04.140 --> 23:05.580
whole assembly with hunger.

23:06.640 --> 23:12.700
Then said the Lord unto Moses, Behold, I will rain bread from heaven for you, and the people

23:12.700 --> 23:17.980
shall go out and gather a certain rate every day, that I may prove them whether they will

23:17.980 --> 23:19.840
walk in my law or no.

23:20.540 --> 23:25.040
And it shall come to pass that on the sixth day they shall prepare that which they bring

23:25.040 --> 23:28.300
in, and it shall be twice as much as they gather daily.

23:29.180 --> 23:35.020
And Moses and Aaron said unto all the children of Israel, At even, then ye shall know that

23:35.020 --> 23:39.840
the Lord hath brought you out from the land of Egypt, and in the morning then ye shall

23:39.840 --> 23:45.420
see the glory of the Lord, for that he heareth your murmurings against the Lord, and what

23:45.420 --> 23:47.560
are we that ye murmur against us?

23:48.520 --> 23:53.420
And Moses said, This shall be when the Lord shall give you in the evening flesh to eat,

23:53.560 --> 23:58.140
and in the morning bread to the full, for that the Lord heareth your murmurings which

23:58.140 --> 24:03.800
ye murmur against him, and what are we, your murmurings are not against us, but against

24:03.800 --> 24:04.320
the Lord.

24:05.220 --> 24:11.060
And Moses spake unto Aaron, Say unto all the congregation of the children of Israel, Come

24:11.060 --> 24:14.380
near before the Lord, for he hath heard your murmurings.

24:15.100 --> 24:19.980
And it came to pass, as Aaron spake unto the whole congregation of the children of Israel,

24:20.240 --> 24:24.740
that they looked toward the wilderness, and behold, the glory of the Lord appeared in

24:24.740 --> 24:25.340
the cloud.

24:26.520 --> 24:31.880
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, I have heard the murmurings of the children of Israel,

24:32.320 --> 24:37.320
speak unto them, saying, At even ye shall eat flesh, and in the morning ye shall be

24:37.320 --> 24:41.240
filled with bread, and ye shall know that I am the Lord your God.

24:42.140 --> 24:47.720
And it came to pass that at even the quails came up and covered the camp, and in the morning

24:47.720 --> 24:49.800
the dew lay round about the host.

24:50.620 --> 24:55.380
And when the dew that lay was gone up, behold, upon the face of the wilderness there lay

24:55.380 --> 24:59.460
a small round thing, as small as the whore-frost on the ground.

25:00.080 --> 25:05.840
And when the children of Israel saw it, they said one to another, It is manna, for they

25:05.840 --> 25:07.240
whisked not what it was.

25:07.760 --> 25:12.440
And Moses said unto them, This is the bread which the Lord hath given you to eat.

25:13.140 --> 25:15.760
This is the thing which the Lord hath commanded.

25:16.440 --> 25:21.920
Gather of it every man according to his eating, and omer for every man according to the number

25:21.920 --> 25:22.860
of your persons.

25:23.560 --> 25:26.320
Take ye every man for them which are in his tents.

25:26.900 --> 25:31.680
And the children of Israel did so, and gathered some more, some less.

25:32.500 --> 25:37.500
And when they did meet it with an omer, he that gathered much had nothing over, and he

25:37.500 --> 25:39.300
that gathered little had no lack.

25:39.760 --> 25:42.100
They gathered every man according to his eating.

25:43.040 --> 25:46.340
And Moses said, Let no man leave of it till the morning.

25:47.800 --> 25:52.600
Notwithstanding they hearkened not unto Moses, but some of them left of it until the morning,

25:52.600 --> 25:56.820
and it bred worms and stank, and Moses was wroth with them.

25:57.860 --> 26:02.200
And they gathered it every morning, every man according to his eating, and when the

26:02.200 --> 26:03.880
sun waxed hot it melted.

26:04.940 --> 26:09.980
And it came to pass that on the sixth day they gathered twice as much bread, two omers

26:09.980 --> 26:14.480
for one man, and all the rulers of the congregation came and told Moses.

26:15.080 --> 26:20.060
And he said unto them, This is that which the Lord hath said, To-morrow is the rest

26:20.060 --> 26:22.080
of the holy Sabbath unto the Lord.

26:22.680 --> 26:28.040
Bake that which ye will bake to-day, and seed that which ye will seed, and that which remaineth

26:28.040 --> 26:30.980
over, lay up for you to be kept until the morning.

26:31.860 --> 26:37.220
And they laid it up till the morning, as Moses bad, and it did not stink, neither was there

26:37.220 --> 26:38.500
any worm therein.

26:39.700 --> 26:46.040
And Moses said, Eat that to-day, for to-day is a Sabbath unto the Lord, to-day ye shall

26:46.040 --> 26:47.460
not find it in the field.

26:48.020 --> 26:53.700
Six days shall ye gather it, but on the seventh day, which is the Sabbath, in it there shall

26:53.700 --> 26:54.320
be none.

26:55.360 --> 27:00.300
And it came to pass that there went out some of the people on the seventh day for to gather,

27:00.600 --> 27:01.920
and they found none.

27:02.920 --> 27:08.420
And the Lord said unto Moses, How long refuse ye to keep my commandments and my laws?

27:09.220 --> 27:14.280
See for that the Lord hath given you the Sabbath, therefore he giveth you on the sixth day

27:14.280 --> 27:20.600
the bread of two days, Abigee, every man in his place, let no man go out of his place

27:20.600 --> 27:21.820
on the seventh day.

27:22.660 --> 27:25.060
So the people rested on the seventh day.

27:26.140 --> 27:31.820
And the house of Israel called the name thereof Manna, and it was like coriander seed, white,

27:32.140 --> 27:34.940
and the taste of it was like wafers made with honey.

27:35.940 --> 27:41.280
And Moses said, This is the thing which the Lord commandeth, fill an omer of it to be

27:41.280 --> 27:45.880
kept for your generations, that they may seed the bread wherewith I have fed you in the

27:45.880 --> 27:49.280
wilderness when I brought you forth from the land of Egypt.

27:50.360 --> 27:55.740
And Moses said unto Aaron, Take a pot and put an omer full of Manna therein, and lay

27:55.740 --> 27:58.720
it up before the Lord to be kept for your generations.

27:59.840 --> 28:04.820
As the Lord commanded Moses, so Aaron laid it up before the testimony to be kept.

28:05.480 --> 28:11.000
And the children of Israel did eat Manna forty years until they came to a land inhabited.

28:11.640 --> 28:15.660
They did eat Manna until they came unto the borders of the land of Canaan.

28:15.660 --> 28:19.460
Now an omer is the tenth part of an ifah.

